lottery /ˈlɒtərɪ/

(lotteries) 

1. N-COUNT A lottery is a type of gambling game in which people buy numbered tickets. Several numbers are then chosen, and the people who have those numbers on their tickets win a prize. 彩票抽奖 

例： ...the national lottery. …全国性的彩票抽奖。 

2. N-SING If you describe something as a lottery , you mean that what happens depends entirely on luck or chance. 靠运气的事 

例： The stockmarket is a lottery. 股市靠的是运气。

